body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting us today. My name is Ryan Parker and I represent XYZ Car Dealership. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Megan. Before we proceed, could you please provide me with your date of birth for security verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's one nine eight zero, July fifteen.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Megan. Additionally, we require your ZIP code to locate your customer profile. Could you share that with me?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's nine zero zero four eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing the information, Megan. We'll now proceed to address your concerns regarding privacy. I understand your surprise and assure you that we take customer privacy very seriously.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Megan. If you have any further questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out. Have a great day!
